Job Description:
The New York City Department of Sanitation (DSNY) keeps New York City healthy, safe, and clean by collecting, recycling, and disposing of waste, cleaning City streets and vacant lots, and clearing snow and ice. DSNY is the nation’s largest municipal sanitation agency, with nearly 10,000 employees, 59 district garages, and a fleet of more than 5,000 trucks, cars and other types of equipment.

The primary responsibilities of this position are:

• Drafting, reviewing and revising contract documents for the implementation of the City’s Covid-19 emergency food distribution program, GetFood and advising on the implementation and administration of these contracts;
• Researching contract and legal issues involving the applicability of laws and regulations affecting the food distribution GetFood program;
• Drafting and reviewing memos and letters to vendors in the GetFood program;
• Drafting contracts and RFPs in connection with general DSNY operations, including for construction and general services;
• Drafting responsiveness and responsibility memoranda and appeals regarding Department contractors;
• Assisting and advising various bureaus regarding contract interpretation, contractor disputes and claims, litigation management, and drafting responses to Contractor protests and appeals;
• Commercial Waste Zones (CWZ) will create a safe and efficient collection system that provide high quality, low cost service to New York City businesses while advancing the Department’s zero waste goals: Advising, drafting and researching legal issues relating to the Request for Proposals (RFP) for Commercial Waste Zones; and
• Conducting legal research and drafting memos on issues concerning the CWZ contracts.

Preferred Skills:
Prefer candidate should possess:
• Excellent writing skills and broad experience in contract drafting;
• Working knowledge of City Procurement Policy Board Rules and City contract procedures;
• Familiarity with commercial waste zone issues and with environmental issues that relate to solid waste management.
